cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.SY, cs.CE, cs.IT 

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on the dynamics of traffic and congestion in a network, and proposes a time-varying network model for communication networks. 
2. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - The paper discusses the effect of network topology on the dynamics of traffic and congestion, and considers the role of betweenness centrality in finding user's shortest route in the network. 
3. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a model for time-varying communication networks and analyzes the optimal data sending rate and critical packet generation rate. 
4. cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science) - The paper uses mathematical modeling and analysis to study the effect of correlations on routing in communication networks. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper considers the capacity of data forwarding links in a network and analyzes the impact of hub nodes on congestion.
